body:
### Component

Forge

### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?

- [X] Foundry
- [X] Foundryup

### What version of Foundry are you on?

forge 0.2.0 (2885b0d 2023-09-13T00:27:42.259884802Z)

### What command(s) is the bug in?

forge fmt

### Operating System

Linux

### Describe the bug

The following code:
```solidity
library MyLib {
    bytes32 private constant TYPE_HASH = keccak256(
        // forgefmt: disable-start
        "MyStruct("
            "uint8 myEnum,"
            "address myAddress"
        ")"
        // forgefmt: disable-end
    );
}
```

Becomes this after format:
```solidity
library MyLib {
    bytes32 private constant TYPE_HASH = keccak256(
        // forgefmt: disable-start
        "MyStruct("
    );
    // forgefmt: disable-end
}
```

### Update

This code behaves properly:
```solidity
    // forgefmt: disable-start
    bytes32 private constant TYPE_HASH = keccak256(
        "MyStruct("
            "uint8 myEnum,"
            "address myAddress"
        ")"
    );
    // forgefmt: disable-end
```
